dialogue.speaker: Bot
dialogue.message: So, what's up with you, wanna talk about photography?

dialogue.speaker: Human
dialogue.message: I do, but I honestly know very little about the subject. Maybe you can help me with that?

dialogue.speaker: Bot
dialogue.message: I'd be happy to help you out - photography's basically capturing images using light and stuff, right?

dialogue.speaker: Human
dialogue.message: I guess I've never broken it down like that. Tell me the story behind the first photograph ever taken.

dialogue.speaker: Bot
dialogue.message: I don't have that info off the top of my head, but I think it was taken by Joseph Nicephore Niepce, and it's pretty old, like from the 1800s or something.

dialogue.speaker: Human
dialogue.message: I wonder what he took a picture of.

dialogue.speaker: Bot
dialogue.message: I think it was a view from his window, but I'm not entirely sure, I'd have to check that out for you.

dialogue.speaker: Human
dialogue.message: That's okay that you don't know everything. I barely know anything about photography. I do love to look at nature photos though,

dialogue.speaker: Bot
dialogue.message: Nature photos are the best, there's something about capturing the beauty of the world that's just amazing, you know?

dialogue.speaker: Human
dialogue.message: It really is. I was obsessed with Ansel Adams when I was in high school. I had his posters on my wall.

dialogue.speaker: Bot
dialogue.message: Ansel Adams is a legend, his black and whites of Yosemite are iconic, I can see why you'd be obsessed!

dialogue.speaker: Human
dialogue.message: Yeah, the one I remember the most was of a waterfall, would you happen to have any idea what waterfall the image was of? I can't remember.

dialogue.speaker: Bot
dialogue.message: I think it might be Vernal Falls, but I'm not 100% sure, he took so many amazing shots of Yosemite!

dialogue.speaker: Human
dialogue.message: You might be right. Did he live near Yosemite?

dialogue.speaker: Bot
dialogue.message: I think he spent a lot of time in Yosemite, but I'm pretty sure he was from San Francisco, or at least lived there for a while.

dialogue.speaker: Human
dialogue.message: Here's a good trivia question that I'd like to learn the answer to. Who was the first US President to have his picture taken?

dialogue.speaker: Bot
dialogue.message: That's a cool question, I think it was John Quincy Adams, but don't quote me on that, haha!

dialogue.speaker: Human
dialogue.message: Okay, I won't tell anyone! I promise. What's better a film camera or a digital camera?

dialogue.speaker: Bot
dialogue.message: Honestly, I think it's a matter of personal preference, some people love the feel of film, while others prefer the convenience of digital.

dialogue.speaker: Human
dialogue.message: That makes sense. When did the first digital cameras come out?

dialogue.speaker: Bot
dialogue.message: I think it was back in the 70s, but they were super primitive and not really like the digital cameras we know today.
